## App Shell Pattern

```html
<div class="udc-nav-header">...</div>
<div style="display:flex; min-height:calc(100vh - 64px);">
  <nav class="udc-nav-vertical" style="width:240px; border-right:1px solid var(--uds-color-border-secondary); padding:var(--uds-space-200) 0;">
    ...nav buttons...
  </nav>
  <main style="flex:1; padding:var(--uds-space-300); overflow-y:auto;">
    ...page content...
  </main>
</div>
```

## Keyboard Patterns

| Component | Behavior |
|-----------|----------|
| Dropdown | ArrowUp/Down navigate, Enter/Space select, Escape close |
| Dialog | Escape close, Tab focus trap, auto-focus on open |
| Tabs | ArrowLeft/Right between tabs, Home/End |
| List | ArrowUp/Down navigate, Enter/Space select |
| Tile | Enter/Space toggle selection |
| Data Table | Enter/Space on header cycles sort |

## Error & Validation

- Validate on **blur**
- Set `data-state="error"` on wrapper
- Replace helper text with error message
- Clear error on next input
- Form-level: `<div class="udc-notification" data-variant="error">...</div>`

## Common Mistakes

```
WRONG: <div style="background: #f5f5f5; padding: 16px; border-radius: 8px;">
RIGHT: <div style="background: var(--uds-color-surface-subtle); padding: var(--uds-space-200); border-radius: var(--uds-border-radius-input);">

WRONG: color: var(--uds-primitive-color-blue-60-M);
RIGHT: color: var(--uds-color-text-interactive);

WRONG: Building a custom modal/popup/select/tag/tooltip from scratch
RIGHT: Use the matching UDS component (see "Common UI Pattern" table above)

WRONG: Copying the example HTML from the doc site as production React/Vue code
RIGHT: Use the framework-agnostic web components from UDS Storybook
       (e.g. <udc-button>, <udc-dialog>, <udc-data-table>) — they work
       in any framework. Reach for raw HTML+classes only as a fallback.

WRONG: Inventing classes like `uds-button`, `myButton`, `udc_button`
RIGHT: Always use the canonical `udc-{component}` BEM names
```

## Custom CSS

For anything UDS doesn't cover, use tokens for ALL values:
```css
.my-hero {
  background: var(--uds-color-surface-subtle);
  padding: var(--uds-space-500) var(--uds-space-300);
  border-radius: var(--uds-border-radius-container-md);
  font-family: var(--uds-font-family);
}
.my-hero h1 {
  font-size: var(--uds-font-size-5xl);
  font-weight: var(--uds-font-weight-bold);
  color: var(--uds-color-text-primary);
}
```

## Compliance Checklist — Verify Before Outputting Code

Before returning ANY code, verify:
- [ ] No hex colors (#xxx), rgb(), or rgba() — use `var(--uds-color-*)`
- [ ] No px for spacing/padding/margin/gap — use `var(--uds-space-*)`
- [ ] No hardcoded font names — use `var(--uds-font-family)`
- [ ] No `--uds-primitive-*` tokens — semantic only
- [ ] No custom components when UDS has an equivalent (check the mapping table)
- [ ] All `udc-*` classes match the canonical names from this rule
- [ ] Interactive components meet the documented keyboard patterns
- [ ] For React/Vue/etc., prefer Storybook web components over copying example HTML

